I left a comment on Brent&#039;s blog, and I feel I need to make another one here, too.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
While I love the MVP community, I feel they are the only ones with enough power to drive product decisions outside of Microsoft. If MVPs are tame, constructive criticism will never get to the PMs and middle-managers at Microsoft that can make a difference. I, for one, expect MVPs to be very vocal, even if their opinion is not popular. &lt;br /&gt;
